        <article class = "text">
            <h3>Discover unknown transformative patterns</h3>
            <p>
                Data science provides businesses with new patterns and trends that 
                have the potential to transform the organization. It can uncover ways 
                to maximize impact on profit margins by implementing low-cost changes. 
                For example, an e-commerce company uses data science to discover that 
                they are receiving excessive customer queries after business hours. 
                Further analysis reveals that providing prompt responses to customers 
                makes them more likely to purchase products. Thus, by implementing 24/7 
                customer service, the business can generate 30% more revenue.
            </p>
        </article>
        <article class = "text">
            <h3>Innovate new products and solutions</h3>
            <p>
                Data science can identify gaps and problems that may otherwise 
                be overlooked. Learning more about purchase decisions, customer 
                feedback, and business processes can stimulate innovation in 
                internal operations and external solutions. For instance, data 
                science is used by an online payment system to compile and examine 
                social media comments made by customers regarding the business. 
                According to the analysis, customers are dissatisfied with the 
                present password retrieval method and forget their credentials 
                during moments of high purchasing activity. By developing a 
                superior solution based on this analysis, the business can 
                significantly improve customer satisfaction.
            </p>
        </article>
        <article class = "text">
            <h3>Real-time optimization</h3>
            <p>
                It is challenging for businesses, especially large corporations, 
                to react quickly to changing circumstances in real-time. This 
                can result in significant losses or interruptions to corporate 
                operations. However, businesses can anticipate change and respond 
                to various situations more effectively with the aid of data science. 
                For instance, data science is used by a truck-based shipping company 
                to minimize downtime when trucks malfunction. They adjust truck 
                schedules by determining which routes and shift patterns result in 
                more frequent breakdowns. In order to speed up vehicle repairs, they 
                also establish an inventory of popular spare parts that require 
                frequent replacement.
            </p>
        </article>
        
